<div id="outline-container-orgbcbed2e" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgbcbed2e">Datacamp</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-orgbcbed2e">
<p>
You can get access to Datacamp via the <a href="https://www.tilburguniversity.edu/students/skills/programming">university website</a>.
</p>

<p>
From Datacamp, do the following courses:
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Intro: <a href="https://www.datacamp.com/courses/intro-to-python-for-data-science">https://www.datacamp.com/courses/intro-to-python-for-data-science</a></li>
<li>Intermediate: <a href="https://www.datacamp.com/courses/intermediate-python-for-data-science">https://www.datacamp.com/courses/intermediate-python-for-data-science</a></li>
<li>Pandas: <a href="https://learn.datacamp.com/courses/data-manipulation-with-pandas">https://learn.datacamp.com/courses/data-manipulation-with-pandas</a></li>
</ul>

<p>
It is up to you how to combine the Datacamp courses with the <a href="./pagescreencasts.html">Screencasts</a>. We suggest to finish the Datacamp Intro course first. As there is no economics on Datacamp, some students prefer to start with the screencasts after the Intro. Others prefer to finish all the Datacamp courses before they start on the screencasts, so that they have seen all the python and pandas material.
</p>
</div>
</div>

